</para>
<para id="element-21">We must also understand here that this relation does not relate linear velocities of the particles constituting the body to that of angular velocity. The linear velocities are, as a matter of fact, different for different particles. The velocities of the particles constituting the body depends on their relative position with respect to the center of mass or the point of contact. Thus, we should bear in mind that above relation specifically connects the linear velocity of center of mass (
