</m:msub>
</m:math>
" that of center of mass"
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mi> C </m:mi>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
". It must be understood that linear velocity of a particle depends on its position on the rim. Farther the position from the point of contact, greater is the velocity. 
</para>
<para id="element-41">In vector notation, the combined velocity of a particle on the rim or anywhere inside the rotating body (as seen in the ground reference) is given by :
</para>
